        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>School Attendance Improves Lives Act of 2015 </b></p> <p> Amends title XVI (Supplemental Security Income) (SSI) of the Social Security Act to condition SSI benefits for disabled children aged 16 or 17 on school attendance, except where the Social Security Administration determines that the individual has good medical cause to not attend school for part or all of a month.</p>]]></text>
